Let me think about this from a different angle. The test failure pattern suggests it's intermittent. Looking at the waitForResponse implementation, I notice something:

```typescript
async waitForResponse(retryCount?: number): Promise<void> {
    // First wait for a response element to appear
    await this.code.waitForElement(CHAT_RESPONSE, undefined, retryCount);

    // Then wait for it to complete (not loading)
    await this.code.waitForElement(CHAT_RESPONSE_COMPLETE, undefined, retryCount);
}
```

The problem is that this waits for ANY response element first, then waits for ANY complete response. But if there are multiple responses on the page (from previous tests or messages), this could match the wrong element! 

Actually, looking at the test more carefully - it's a fresh test that just sent "Hello", so there should only be one response. Unless... let me check if the test properly cleans up between runs.

